        verification storyScopeAwareAuthoringDoD : Test { :>> id = "63940516-2c7d-4e8f-c245-51627384c002"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::demo; :>> procedureText = "Delivers srViewerRelationshipGrammar + srViewerScopedAuthoring (D0126, governed by D0127) — the human's (2026-07-17) scope/process-aware creation. KEEL (v1.16.0, fe54cc7): view::grammar_json / GET /api/grammar computes the relationship grammar as a VIEW — the distinct (sourceType, edge, targetType) triples OBSERVED in the model + a per-type up/down summary (48 triples). No authored metamodel, no schema/core change; read per-connected-project so it is generic across domains (deliverable vocab stays downstream, §1). VIEWER (f860b5f): (1) SCOPE-AWARE New-item — when the view is scoped (a solo'd register type, else the types present in the graph), the type picker offers ONLY in-scope types + the types they interface with (grammar up/down), with a 'show all types' escape; unscoped shows the full list. (2) GRAMMAR-CONSTRAINED Connect — the edge-kind select narrows to the kinds OBSERVED for the (from,to) type pair; an unobserved pair falls back to the full closed algebra (authoring a new-but-valid pattern still allowed). VERIFY (demo, live): scope=SystemRequirement -> picker = {Component, Decision, Need, Story, SubsystemRequirement, SystemRequirement} (SR + its grammar neighbours, NOT all 91); Need->SR connect kinds = [satisfy] (the sole observed pattern), SR->Need falls back to the full algebra. This realises the human's safety/STPA example generically: a safety scope would offer Loss Scenario / up-Loss / down-Requirement, never a bare Need. clippy + validate + guard + check-engine green. NOTE: D0127 is PROPOSED — its acceptance is the human's end-of-sitting per-sitting review."; }
        part storyScopeAwareAuthoringDoDR1 : TestResult { :>> id = "63940516-2c7d-4e8f-c245-51627384c003"; :>> outcome = VerdictKind::pass; :>> judgedAgainst = "fe54cc7"; :>> judgedAt = "2026-07-17"; :>> judgedBy = "claudeOpus"; }
    }

