    verification saReviewGate : Test { :>> id = "63940516-2c7d-4e8f-c245-51627384c00a"; :>> title = "Sprint 245 review gate"; :>> createdAt = "2026-07-17"; :>> createdBy = "claudeOpus"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::inspect; :>> procedureText = "Reviewed. Grammar-as-computed-view keeps the engine invariant (everything derivable is a view) + avoids freezing schema — an elegant fit. Scope-aware creation is honestly gated (scope from the active lens; full-list escape preserved). Connect stays permissive on unobserved pairs (won't block a valid new pattern) while nudging to observed ones. The D0127 acceptance is correctly LEFT for the human (proposed, not fabricated). Clean."; }
